{
  "texts": [
    "One year later, the same supervised classification task was tested, this time employing CNNs (Mohammadi et al., 2023).",
    "Two models were created to predict the percentage of CM content on Day 10 of differentiation, using pre-differentiation experimental features and nondestructive images from Days 3 or 5.",
    "One CNN utilized only phase-contrast image, while another incorporated a combination of both images and the features identified in earlier work (Mohammadi et al., 2022).",
    "With an accuracy of 85% and precision of 92%, the best-performing model was the combination CNN using images from Day 5, outperforming the other ML models, including GP with features only, SVM with images only, and SVM with a combination of images and features.",
    "Although successful on only about 300 images, the model developed a dependence on the specific cell line used."
  ]
}